Hong Kong Visitors Spending Rises to Record High of $27 Billion

-- B y   W e n d y   L e u n g
-- 
2011-04-03T11:19:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/hong-kong-visitors-spending-rises-to-record-high-of-27-billion.html
Tourists to  Hong Kong  spent a record
HK$210 billion ($27 billion) last year on rising income from
Chinese visitors.  Spending in 2010 jumped 33 percent from a year earlier, the
city’s tourism board said in a  statement  on it’s website today.
Per capita spending of overnight tourists increased by 17
percent to HK$6,728, it said.  Same-day visitors from mainland  China  made the highest
spending per capita, the statement said. Visitor arrivals from
China to the former British colony jumped 26 percent from a year
earlier to 22.7 million in 2010, the tourism board said in
February. A record 36 million tourists visited the city last
year, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Leung in Hong Kong at 
